X:1
T:Instrument-sound mapping test
C:addInstrumentSounds regression
% Verifies addInstrumentSounds(): every part gets the right MusicXML <instrument-sound>.
% Exercises the tricky disambiguations that depend on most-specific-first ordering:
%   bass clarinet vs clarinet, piccolo trumpet vs trumpet, english horn vs (french) horn,
%   contrabass (string) vs basses (voice).
% Expected ids: wind.flutes.flute, wind.reed.clarinet.bass, wind.reed.english-horn,
%   brass.french-horn, brass.trumpet.piccolo, strings.contrabass, voice.bass.
% Check: grep -c '<instrument-sound>' out.xml   == number of parts (7).
M:4/4
L:1/4
K:C
V:V1 name="Flute 1"
V:V2 name="Bass Clarinet"
V:V3 name="English Horn"
V:V4 name="Horn in F 1"
V:V5 name="Piccolo Trumpet"
V:V6 name="Contrabasses"
V:V7 name="Basses"
[V:V1] CDEF|
[V:V2] CDEF|
[V:V3] CDEF|
[V:V4] CDEF|
[V:V5] CDEF|
[V:V6] C,D,E,F,|
[V:V7] C,D,E,F,|
